          <li class="mb-4">
            <strong>Step 1- Brake Fluid Level And Quality Check</strong>
            <p>We begin by checking the brake fluid. The fluid is what helps to pass on the pressure when you press on the brake pedal. If it's low or dirty, it may weaken or slow down your brakes.</p>
            <p>We will change the brake fluid if it is aged or not working correctly. Fresh fluid guarantees that your brakes react immediately and identically each time.</p>
